SUPER USEFUL COMMAND!
# wc is wordcount command (lines, words, characters counted)
# find ~ -name "*" -print | grep README | wc -l ---> looks through all files in directory - finds the ones with README in title and then counts the number of LINES given to wc: ie number of files with README in title
wc -l <filename> print the line count (note that if the last line does not have \n, it will not be counted)
wc -c <filename> print the byte count
wc -m <filename> print the character count
wc -L <filename> print the length of longest line
wc -w <filename> print the word count
